hopobject.body: I'm training to be an engineer wwww.labimed.com.br Did Trayvon make a stupid mistake when he doubled back and took Zimmerman on? Yes, he did. But Zimmerman made a stupid mistake when he got out of his vehicle. Both were bad choices. I understand what Trayvon did. He really didn't want to run in fear from some stranger in the dark. If he had been a little older and a little smarter, he would have run, because that's the best thing to do. But he was young and full of testosterone and macho, so he figured he would show this stalker not to mess with him. I also understand what Zimmerman did. He wanted to be a hero. He wanted to be the guy that everyone admired for his courage. Unfortunately, part of his courage was embodied in a gun. When things didn't go the way he planned, he chose to use that gun. Tragically, a young man died.
